<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Why does everyone always forget bards?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Tarwen">Tarwen</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:26 a.m. 24/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Why does everyone always forget bards?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1158" TARGET=_self>The hybrids are an embarrasment</A> (TheBlack[BCK])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Is it because bards are awesome and *fun* hybrids to play? :) I don't know how well they are balanced for pvp but they sure are balanced for general game play. Im sure they will be good for pvp. At lvl 4 they get that nice running man song, and later at lvl 10 they can make your group's melee attack much faster. Paladins, SKs, and rangers aren't the only hybrids, dont leave out the bards!

<P>&gt; In terms of game balance and PvP the hybrids are sort of a joke.
<BR>&gt; SKs round out the bottom of the barrel. Paladins still seem to
<BR>&gt; have their place, even in PvP, in the low to mid levels since
<BR>&gt; they can do that wonderful heal 1x a day. Perhaps at higher
<BR>&gt; levels Rangers with dual wield might come into their own, but
<BR>&gt; the spellcasting abilities of the hybrids are a joke. They were
<BR>&gt; a joke when they were first introduced into AD&D and they are a
<BR>&gt; joke here. No one ever bothered to rectify the situation in AD&D
<BR>&gt; becuase, lets face it, how many characters do you play in AD&D
<BR>&gt; that are beyond 12th level?
<P>&gt; The Hybrids could be saved if they received spells that are
<BR>&gt; equal in power to casters of the same level, or possibly cast at
<BR>&gt; one or two levels lower. Reduce the selection of spells if
<BR>&gt; needed to further balance it out, but for example a 20th Paladin
<BR>&gt; should cast somewhere in the neighborhood of 18th for the spell
<BR>&gt; to make sense. I don't expect so see any real changes to these
<BR>&gt; hybrid classes in spite of the loud and frequent griping by
<BR>&gt; those that favor them. Verant seems to think they have them
<BR>&gt; nailed down, and perhaps they do for PvE. For PvP I think
<BR>&gt; Paladins are good low-mid, and Rangers *may* be viable now with
<BR>&gt; dual wield. SKs are right out, except perhaps at really low
<BR>&gt; levels where that 10hp x level damage spell might come in handy
<BR>&gt; :-)
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
